Having spent approx $60,000 on the home internally the current owner have recently rebuilt the kitchen, bathroom, bedrooms and living areas. The electrical wiring, plasterwork and fencing have also been recently replaced.
The homes features include redone polished floors, 3 bedrooms, separate study, high ceilings and a Coonara wood fire.
For further information or to arrange your personal inspection time please contact Tamara Clancy on 0420 827 286 or Jason Dowler on 0403 598 754 anytime.

Description:
1/4 Acre...A Natural Beauty
Dappled sunlight reveals a unique family home designed to blend with it's natural environment.
Set in a popular treed location and employing a variety of building materials in a heavy post and beam construction, this home features solid mud-brick walls that insulate beautifully.
With over 20 squares, the striking interior features bright North facing living overlooked by a mezzanine level that joins the upstairs wings.
Family sized kitchen and meals with twin drawer dishwasher and gas stove features solid blackwood tops.
3 bedrooms + study with upstairs parents retreat main and full ensuite, separate rumpus/sitting and central feature
heat-wall with blazing coonara heater.
Outside:
Explore a private front courtyard - great for kids/dogs, brick paved pergola and huge rear yard with 20 X 40' garage and additional office attached - a real family escape.
